WEBVTT

00:00.478 --> 00:05.440
♪

00:30.117 --> 00:36.775
♪ atmospheric music

02:16.048 --> 02:18.138
[buzzer]

02:18.181 --> 02:20.575
[distorted male voice
on intercom]

02:20.618 --> 02:23.143
I'm Anna Troyev,
the art therapy instructor.

02:25.623 --> 02:27.408
[buzzer]

02:42.988 --> 02:44.816
Arms up.

02:53.085 --> 02:54.957
I trust we won't go
through this every day.

02:56.393 --> 02:57.177
Male voice: Anna?

02:59.048 --> 03:00.354
Welcome.

03:00.397 --> 03:02.530
Are you ready for
your first day?

03:02.573 --> 03:03.661
I think so.

03:03.705 --> 03:05.837
Please.

03:05.881 --> 03:07.622
Do you live far?

03:07.665 --> 03:10.407
Somewhat, but it's worth it.

03:11.713 --> 03:13.193
I've always wanted to
use art to help people.

03:13.236 --> 03:14.455
Wonderful.

03:14.498 --> 03:15.195
Please.

03:17.284 --> 03:18.850
This way.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.680
Those are our
security procedures.

03:22.724 --> 03:24.943
Learn them backwards
and forwards.

03:26.989 --> 03:29.252
Most of our patients are
quite docile, but others..

03:29.296 --> 03:31.820
Doctor, it's Leena.

03:31.863 --> 03:34.257
She's not in her room,
nobody can find her.

03:34.301 --> 03:36.085
[speaking in Estonian]

03:36.128 --> 03:37.782
Lock it.

03:37.826 --> 03:39.001
[alarm sounds]

03:39.044 --> 03:40.785
Full on lock out!

03:40.829 --> 03:44.049
[alarm sounds]

03:49.751 --> 03:52.623
Who is Leena?

03:52.667 --> 03:55.017
Our most dangerous patient.

03:55.060 --> 03:57.672
In fact, she's the reason
for the opening you're filling.

03:58.542 --> 04:02.285
Your predecessor underestimated
her and ignored protocol.

04:02.329 --> 04:03.895
It did not end well.

04:05.288 --> 04:06.202
Listen to me.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.986
Do not leave this room.

04:08.030 --> 04:09.510
Don't worry, you'll
be safe here

04:09.553 --> 04:11.468
and I'll come back after
we found her.

04:12.339 --> 04:13.731
Please, please.

04:38.974 --> 04:40.323
Hello there.

04:46.460 --> 04:48.766
Does your mom
or dad work here?

04:56.165 --> 04:57.514
Could I see?

05:08.220 --> 05:09.570
Is that me?

05:12.529 --> 05:13.922
That's very good.

05:15.184 --> 05:17.012
I'm Anna.

05:17.055 --> 05:18.361
What's your name?

05:26.891 --> 05:28.458
Leena.

05:31.418 --> 05:34.551
You didn't
a-answer me before.

05:34.595 --> 05:35.857
Do your parents work here?

05:36.423 --> 05:38.860
Why would you think that?

05:42.211 --> 05:44.344
- Because you're..
- I'm what?

05:46.433 --> 05:48.522
[door buzzes]

05:49.914 --> 05:51.960
Leena..

05:52.003 --> 05:53.614
[speaking in Estonian]

05:59.750 --> 06:01.230
Put it down.

06:04.755 --> 06:08.585
Leena, put it down now.

06:24.558 --> 06:26.516
Anna: You didn't tell me
she was a child.

06:27.474 --> 06:29.650
Dr. Novotny: It's
because she's not.

06:29.693 --> 06:34.350
Leena suffers
from a gland disorder.

06:34.394 --> 06:37.875
Which causes
proportional dwarfism,

06:37.919 --> 06:41.749
essentially halting her
growth around age ten.

06:41.792 --> 06:44.360
Make no mistake, Leena may
look like a child,

06:44.404 --> 06:46.580
but she is a grown woman.

06:46.623 --> 06:48.625
31 to be exact.

06:49.800 --> 06:53.717
When Leena first arrived,
she struggled so hard against

06:53.761 --> 06:59.331
her restraints that she
would bleed severely.

06:59.375 --> 07:02.987
It was a lesson for all of
us on the depths of her

07:03.031 --> 07:04.641
will to be free.

07:07.296 --> 07:10.604
Much of Leena's early life
was spent doing whatever she

07:10.647 --> 07:12.910
could to survive.

07:12.954 --> 07:17.132
But she never grew older, at
least not on the outside.

07:17.175 --> 07:19.090
Imagine, going through
your whole life

07:19.134 --> 07:22.137
with the world only
seeing a child.

07:22.877 --> 07:25.619
It is very important that you
do not see her in that way.

07:25.662 --> 07:29.318
Leena uses her affliction as
much as she suffers from it.

07:29.361 --> 07:33.844
She's an exceptional
con artist.

07:35.150 --> 07:39.328
Two years ago, Leena wormed
her way into this family

07:39.371 --> 07:41.330
by posing as a runaway.

07:41.373 --> 07:45.247
This family took her in, they
fed her, they clothed her.

07:45.290 --> 07:47.902
Normally, Leena would simply
steal whatever she could and

07:47.945 --> 07:52.167
disappear, but this time she...

07:54.517 --> 07:59.435
Well, let me put it this
way, she lives here now.

08:24.329 --> 08:25.896
Idti.

08:31.423 --> 08:33.382
[screaming]

08:38.387 --> 08:40.041
Idti!

08:48.571 --> 08:50.399
She does that.

09:14.075 --> 09:16.207
Girl on TV: How much
longer we got, daddy?

09:16.251 --> 09:18.253
Man on TV: You have a
few minutes, darling.

09:18.296 --> 09:20.603
You learning me by
heart little Sara?

09:20.647 --> 09:23.606
Girl on TV: No, daddy, I
know you by heart.

09:23.650 --> 09:26.217
You're inside my heart.

09:28.916 --> 09:31.266
Man on TV: We're going to be
brave, aren't we?

09:31.309 --> 09:32.049
Girl on TV: Yes, daddy.

09:33.660 --> 09:35.096
Man on TV: But this is gonna
be our hardest battle.

09:39.187 --> 09:41.668
Leena; Hello, Dmitri.

09:43.495 --> 09:44.801
You're on time.

09:51.025 --> 09:52.417
It's perfect.

10:04.691 --> 10:06.693
I can't tie these myself.

10:27.017 --> 10:29.063
I want to do
something nice for you.

10:30.238 --> 10:31.631
You can come in.

10:33.328 --> 10:35.678
Yeah. Yeah.

10:35.722 --> 10:38.420
[door buzzes]

10:38.463 --> 10:41.858
[TV sound contines]

11:17.764 --> 11:19.156
Girl on TV: I can do it now.

11:20.418 --> 11:22.725
Any moment I may see, my
daddy coming back to me.

11:24.335 --> 11:26.642
I don't.

11:26.686 --> 11:28.339
My daddy has to go away.

11:34.128 --> 11:37.697
♪ dramatic music

11:49.143 --> 11:50.535
[door lock buzzes]

11:50.579 --> 11:57.499
♪

12:21.828 --> 12:23.394
[Sudden bang]

12:23.438 --> 12:29.183
♪

13:15.098 --> 13:17.013
[Elevator bell dings]

13:22.366 --> 13:23.541
♪

13:25.413 --> 13:29.243
[speaking Estonian]

13:30.244 --> 13:35.205
[speaking Estonian]

13:38.948 --> 13:40.384
Idti.

13:41.298 --> 13:42.473
Do you want some candy?

14:04.974 --> 14:07.281
[Alarm]

14:11.154 --> 14:13.417
Idti!

14:13.461 --> 14:17.334
♪ Tense music

14:30.478 --> 14:32.959
♪ Tense music

14:48.626 --> 14:49.801
She cut the feed.

14:52.979 --> 14:54.545
I'm so sorry, Anna.

14:55.677 --> 14:58.506
Hopefully, the police will find
her before anyone else is hurt.

15:01.074 --> 15:03.467
Not quite the start we'd
hoped for, I'm sure.

15:05.121 --> 15:07.080
This job isn't for me.

15:27.274 --> 15:32.627
♪

15:58.783 --> 16:05.051
[trunk opens, car makes
pinging sound ]

16:09.011 --> 16:11.753
♪ tense music

16:43.132 --> 16:47.267
[musical crash]

16:50.009 --> 16:51.575
♪ soft piano

17:12.640 --> 17:16.339
[piano builds to
intense playing]

17:16.383 --> 17:19.081
♪

18:08.174 --> 18:09.349
[music stops]

18:18.445 --> 18:21.100
[groaning]

18:23.841 --> 18:25.452
Oh, Anna.

18:26.888 --> 18:28.324
It usually takes only one.

18:44.340 --> 18:45.559
[Speaking Estonian]
Who's there?

18:50.781 --> 18:52.000
Don't be afraid,
I'm police.

18:53.001 --> 18:54.133
[In English]
Don't be afraid, I'm police.

18:59.355 --> 19:00.313
Uh...Where are your parents?

19:01.705 --> 19:03.316
My parents are in America.

19:05.492 --> 19:07.842
Sweetheart,
what is your name?

19:10.845 --> 19:13.500
My name is Esther.

19:26.904 --> 19:28.167
♪ You're coming with me

19:28.210 --> 19:30.081
♪

19:30.125 --> 19:32.823
♪ Through the aging the
fear and the strife ♪

19:32.867 --> 19:33.955
♪

19:33.998 --> 19:35.565
♪ It's the smiling
on the package ♪

19:35.609 --> 19:36.784
♪ It's the faces in the sand

19:36.827 --> 19:38.133
♪

19:38.177 --> 19:39.482
♪ It's the thought that
moves you upwards ♪

19:39.526 --> 19:40.918
♪ Embracing me with two hands

19:40.962 --> 19:41.876
♪

19:41.919 --> 19:43.094
♪ Right will take you places

19:43.138 --> 19:43.834
♪ Yeah maybe to the beach

19:43.878 --> 19:45.096
♪

19:45.140 --> 19:46.924
♪ When your friends
they do come crying ♪

19:46.968 --> 19:50.101
♪ Tell 'em now your pleasure's
set upon slow release ♪

19:50.145 --> 19:52.016
♪

19:52.060 --> 19:52.930
♪ Hey wait

19:52.974 --> 19:54.845
♪

19:54.889 --> 20:00.416
♪ Great smile sensitive
to fate not ♪

20:00.460 --> 20:03.027
♪

20:03.071 --> 20:06.205
♪ It took a lifespan
with no cellmate ♪

20:06.248 --> 20:07.162
♪

20:07.206 --> 20:09.860
♪ The long way back

20:09.904 --> 20:11.210
♪

20:11.253 --> 20:15.301
♪ Sandy why can't we
look the other way? ♪

20:15.344 --> 20:16.954
♪

20:18.565 --> 20:20.480
- You killed it.
- Thanks, man.

20:20.523 --> 20:21.785
Proud of you, sweetheart.

20:21.829 --> 20:23.134
Yeah, great job, pal.

20:23.178 --> 20:24.135
Thanks, guys.

20:24.179 --> 20:25.659
How long do you
think you'll be?

20:25.702 --> 20:28.923
Actually a bunch of people are
getting together tonight.

20:28.966 --> 20:30.316
Well, congrats.

20:30.359 --> 20:32.753
I'll see you guys
back at the house.

20:34.798 --> 20:36.800
Allen: I mean, this was
supposed to be family night.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.889
Tricia: What, is he not supposed
to have fun with friends?

20:38.933 --> 20:40.761
Oh God, all he does is have fun.

20:40.804 --> 20:42.284
No.

20:42.328 --> 20:44.199
Gunnar works his tail off.

20:44.721 --> 20:47.289
When he's not studying,
he's fencing.

20:47.333 --> 20:48.377
He's living his life.

20:52.076 --> 20:54.775
Don't do that,
don't go into your head.

20:54.818 --> 20:56.777
I need you to be present.

20:56.820 --> 20:58.039
Gunnar needs you.

20:58.082 --> 20:59.519
Oh, sorry, was I
not at that match?

20:59.562 --> 21:01.956
Esther's not
coming back, Allen.

21:03.000 --> 21:04.175
I miss her too.

21:04.219 --> 21:05.307
I do.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.440
Every moment of every day.

21:12.053 --> 21:13.881
What's he doing here?

21:13.924 --> 21:18.799
♪ melancholy music

21:25.284 --> 21:29.331
[soft conversation,
Esther is mentioned]

21:29.375 --> 21:35.903
♪

21:54.487 --> 21:55.966
Woman: From the little we've
gotten from Esther,

21:56.010 --> 21:58.404
we believe a woman
abducted her, brought her to

21:58.447 --> 22:01.015
Russia and passed her off as
her own child until Esther

22:01.058 --> 22:03.234
managed to escape.

22:04.018 --> 22:05.498
We haven't gotten
many specifics yet.

22:05.541 --> 22:07.456
Perhaps when she's feeling
safer, she can shed some more

22:07.500 --> 22:09.066
light on what
she's been through.

22:10.503 --> 22:13.506
We have a child therapist
that she'll be working with.

22:13.549 --> 22:15.072
Good.

22:15.943 --> 22:17.597
But what she needs
right now is her family.

22:19.468 --> 22:21.165
Be prepared for changes.

22:22.776 --> 22:25.605
Four years is a long time
in the development of a child.

22:26.649 --> 22:29.652
[plays a few notes on piano]

22:46.887 --> 22:48.367
Esther?

22:50.151 --> 22:55.678
Sweetheart, it's
me, it's mommy.

23:03.773 --> 23:06.559
Can I, can I see you?

23:26.013 --> 23:27.754
Sweetie.

23:27.797 --> 23:29.146
It's mommy.

23:37.328 --> 23:39.461
I thought I'd
never see you again.

23:41.376 --> 23:43.552
Everything is right now.

23:47.382 --> 23:49.732
It's been so long since
you've seen any of us.

23:50.690 --> 23:54.433
See if I can..
Oh, there's daddy.

23:55.129 --> 23:57.218
This was one of
our charity events.

23:57.261 --> 23:59.525
He looks so handsome that
night, didn't he?

23:59.568 --> 24:00.656
Stewardess: Can I grab
you anything else?

24:00.700 --> 24:02.441
- No, thanks.
- Okay.

24:04.225 --> 24:06.401
Oh, speak of the devil, your
brother is probably a foot

24:06.445 --> 24:09.099
taller than you'd remember.

24:10.840 --> 24:12.146
Oh, there's Mup-Mup.

24:12.189 --> 24:13.626
She's been so good to us.

24:13.669 --> 24:14.844
Oh, I can't wait to see her.

24:17.499 --> 24:19.588
No, sweetie.

24:19.632 --> 24:21.198
She passed.

24:21.242 --> 24:22.286
Remember?

24:22.330 --> 24:24.375
It's just the four of us now.

24:26.029 --> 24:28.031
I have to use the restroom.

24:34.168 --> 24:35.474
Ah, is the
restroom over there?

24:36.692 --> 24:37.911
Stewardess: No, it's just
right back over there.

24:37.954 --> 24:38.781
Over in the back?

24:38.825 --> 24:40.043
Hm-hm.

24:40.087 --> 24:42.437
- Thank you for your help.
- You're welcome.

24:53.579 --> 24:54.493
I can't wait to see you.

24:54.536 --> 24:55.885
So stupid.

25:20.519 --> 25:23.826
Oh, daddy and Gunnar are
just downstairs.

25:23.870 --> 25:26.916
Do you think father
will recognize me?

25:28.788 --> 25:31.617
Maybe not if you keep
calling him father.

25:31.660 --> 25:32.574
Dad.

25:32.618 --> 25:33.532
Yeah. That's better.

25:35.838 --> 25:38.101
Here, let me look at you.

25:40.539 --> 25:45.413
Oh, my God, you look,
like a little lady.

25:45.456 --> 25:47.415
You've grown up so much.

25:49.243 --> 25:51.941
Take this off.

25:51.985 --> 25:54.422
That's better.
It's less austere.

25:55.902 --> 25:56.598
This is..

26:03.823 --> 26:05.041
Sorry.

26:05.085 --> 26:10.481
No, I-I'm sorry, I..
Come on, let's go.

26:21.188 --> 26:24.757
[airport announcement]

26:31.720 --> 26:33.940
I think, I'm nervous.

26:35.376 --> 26:36.986
Right, big step.

26:40.424 --> 26:41.817
Daddy.

26:43.123 --> 26:46.735
I'm so sorry, I can't
believe it's really you.

26:56.702 --> 26:57.833
I always knew.

26:58.573 --> 26:59.922
I always knew.

27:05.058 --> 27:06.233
Hello, Gunnar.

27:07.277 --> 27:08.670
Hey.

27:09.584 --> 27:11.107
I think we can do a little
better than "hey,"

27:11.151 --> 27:11.978
don't you think?

27:13.327 --> 27:15.242
Come on.

27:20.639 --> 27:21.944
Glad you're back.

27:21.988 --> 27:23.119
Me too.

27:25.252 --> 27:26.427
How about we go home?

27:26.470 --> 27:29.082
- Yes!
- Let's go home.

27:29.125 --> 27:35.088
♪

28:12.473 --> 28:14.083
Tricia: Welcome home, Esther.

28:33.668 --> 28:36.236
We left it
just as it was.

28:36.279 --> 28:38.151
We always knew you'd
come back home.

28:40.457 --> 28:43.634
I mean you probably outgrown
so much but we have a lot of

28:43.678 --> 28:47.769
Christmases and birthdays to
make up for, so just let us

28:47.813 --> 28:50.032
know what you're into,
and you might get it.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.122
I like painting.

28:53.166 --> 28:54.602
You like to paint?

28:54.645 --> 28:56.604
You were never interested
in painting before.

28:58.127 --> 29:00.042
Tricia: Well, maybe you two can
spend some time in your studio.

29:00.086 --> 29:01.609
Allen: Nothing would
make me happier.

29:07.441 --> 29:12.272
♪ record plays

29:12.315 --> 29:17.103
So um, the plan is, tomorrow
you're gonna talk to Dr. Segar.

29:17.146 --> 29:18.408
Do you remember her?

29:18.452 --> 29:22.021
She, she had the
parrot named Sydney?

29:22.064 --> 29:24.327
Hm-hm.

29:24.371 --> 29:27.026
Well, if you need anything..

29:27.069 --> 29:28.244
We're be right down the hall.
Alright?

29:28.288 --> 29:31.378
♪ And let your poor heart
break a little ♪

29:31.421 --> 29:32.814
♪

29:32.858 --> 29:34.598
♪ That's the story of

29:34.642 --> 29:35.512
♪

29:35.556 --> 29:37.558
♪ That's the glory of love

29:37.601 --> 29:41.388
♪

29:41.431 --> 29:43.825
♪ You've got to laugh a little

29:43.869 --> 29:44.565
♪

29:44.608 --> 29:46.262
♪ Cry a little

29:46.306 --> 29:47.568
♪

29:47.611 --> 29:51.224
♪ Before the clouds
roll by a little ♪

29:51.267 --> 29:52.529
♪

29:52.573 --> 29:54.227
♪ That's the story of

29:54.270 --> 29:55.141
♪

29:55.184 --> 29:57.534
♪ That's the glory of love

29:57.578 --> 30:02.496
♪

30:11.679 --> 30:13.202
Receptionist:
Okay, you can go in.

30:13.246 --> 30:15.161
Dr. Segar will be
right with you.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.771
Dr, Segar: I'm seeing her
in few minutes.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.947
I think it's too soon for you
to get involved, detective.

30:18.991 --> 30:21.167
I'd like to talk
to her alone first.

30:21.210 --> 30:23.343
Look, I have to go.

30:37.792 --> 30:39.881
Dr. Segar: You have no idea how
happy I am to see you, Esther.

30:41.056 --> 30:42.318
Welcome home.

30:43.929 --> 30:46.888
Well now, you are certainly not
the little girl I once knew.

30:47.933 --> 30:49.282
You're a young lady now.

30:51.632 --> 30:52.676
Do you remember
what I told you

30:52.720 --> 30:53.895
when we first began
our sessions?

30:56.463 --> 30:57.899
I told you if I ask any
questions that make you

30:57.943 --> 31:00.119
uncomfortable, we'll stop.

31:00.902 --> 31:02.425
I wish my parents
were like you.

31:02.948 --> 31:05.037
How so?

31:05.733 --> 31:07.300
Leena: They keep asking
what happened to me,

31:07.343 --> 31:10.477
but I'm not ready to
tell them about it.

31:10.520 --> 31:12.044
Dr. Segar: And that's
perfectly fine.

31:12.087 --> 31:14.307
I am hoping you'll talk
to me about it,

31:14.350 --> 31:16.570
but only when
you're ready, okay?

31:17.963 --> 31:20.400
Having said that, is there
anything you want to tell me

31:20.443 --> 31:23.751
about your time, away..

31:23.794 --> 31:25.535
You want to play, Sydney?

31:25.579 --> 31:27.755
I think Sydney
wants to play with me.

31:28.147 --> 31:30.453
Hello. I remember you.

31:30.497 --> 31:33.108
Do you remember me?

31:34.240 --> 31:35.632
Your turn.

31:35.676 --> 31:36.895
Esther, you can wait out
here, I'm just gonna need to

31:36.938 --> 31:38.505
talk to your mom for a moment.

31:55.739 --> 31:56.958
Hello.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.438
Woman: Hi.

31:58.481 --> 31:59.613
Leena: I like your earrings.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.832
Woman: Oh, thank you, honey.

32:01.876 --> 32:02.833
What are you writing?

32:02.877 --> 32:04.748
Oh! I'm sorry.

32:04.792 --> 32:06.185
I'm so sorry.

32:06.228 --> 32:07.099
Woman: It's-it's okay.

32:07.142 --> 32:08.404
I'm sorry.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.102
Woman: I'm just gonna
get this cleaned up.

32:19.546 --> 32:21.635
Dr. Segar: Does she seem the
same as you remember?

32:21.678 --> 32:23.376
Different?

32:23.419 --> 32:27.032
Well, of course
she's different.

32:27.075 --> 32:29.512
Dr. Segar: She has
an accent now.

32:29.556 --> 32:34.300
Is that unusual, considering
where she's been?

32:35.083 --> 32:36.258
Dr. Segar: Not necessarily,
she was there a long time

32:36.302 --> 32:38.347
when her speech was still
developing.

32:38.391 --> 32:41.176
But I will tell you,
she's in far better shape

32:41.220 --> 32:44.353
intellectually and emotionally
than I would expect.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.312
Tricia: That's good, right?

32:52.057 --> 32:54.320
Dr. Segar: I did also notice
some inconsistencies.

32:54.363 --> 32:56.583
For example, she
said that was Sydney.

32:56.626 --> 33:00.108
Sydney was a macaw, bright
orange and four times the size.

33:00.152 --> 33:02.241
Yet, today, she addressed
this bird as Sydney

33:02.284 --> 33:04.025
with complete confidence.

33:04.069 --> 33:05.548
What are you getting at?

33:05.592 --> 33:07.289
Dr. Segar: To me, it felt
like a performance.

33:07.333 --> 33:09.248
[squarking]

33:10.640 --> 33:13.382
He hit me and
ripped my dress!

33:13.426 --> 33:15.036
I want to go home.

33:16.429 --> 33:17.821
Tricia: That's enough for today.

33:17.865 --> 33:18.866
Dr. Segar: Of course,
we'll reschedule.

33:39.017 --> 33:40.670
Tricia: Esther, you alright?

33:40.714 --> 33:42.063
Uh, yes.

33:53.161 --> 33:54.597
Hey!

33:55.250 --> 33:56.991
Morticia.

33:57.035 --> 33:58.297
Get Gunnar for me, would you?

33:58.340 --> 33:59.646
What did you call me?

33:59.689 --> 34:02.083
Mike, that's her. The sister?

34:02.127 --> 34:04.520
Oh, shit, it's my bad.

34:04.564 --> 34:07.132
Umm...Get Gunnar.

34:07.175 --> 34:08.524
Pajalsta?

34:10.570 --> 34:12.093
How about I cut your balls off,
and feed them to you,

34:12.137 --> 34:14.095
you fucking shitstain?

34:16.184 --> 34:18.056
Was that Spanish,
or something?

34:18.099 --> 34:19.057
I don't.. Hey.

34:19.100 --> 34:20.406
Let's go.

34:20.841 --> 34:22.103
Your sister's a
fucking trip, man.

34:22.147 --> 34:23.713
Seriously, dude, my
dad's right there.

34:23.757 --> 34:25.063
I don't care.

34:25.106 --> 34:28.805
Mike, what the fuck..
I am what I am.

34:29.980 --> 34:32.113
Hey, honey, you okay?

34:32.157 --> 34:34.028
Hm. My dress is ruined.

34:34.072 --> 34:35.638
We'll buy you a new one.

34:35.682 --> 34:37.249
I was thinking, uh,
just thinking

34:37.292 --> 34:38.641
we can go to the studio.

34:38.685 --> 34:40.469
I would love to.

34:51.306 --> 34:52.525
If I didn't know any better,

34:52.568 --> 34:54.527
I'd think you've never
been in here before.

34:57.878 --> 34:59.575
So beautiful.

35:04.232 --> 35:05.233
Leena: What's the light for?

35:06.713 --> 35:08.062
What's the light for?

35:08.845 --> 35:10.369
So you don't remember?

35:10.412 --> 35:11.631
This is what your
papa is famous for.

35:12.327 --> 35:13.415
Hmm.

35:13.807 --> 35:15.504
Here.

35:15.548 --> 35:17.550
Press on this.

35:24.252 --> 35:26.950
Yeah, I always try to
fit so much in to one canvas,

35:26.994 --> 35:31.129
you know, So I resorted
to a hidden layer.

35:31.781 --> 35:33.087
Nothing is ever just
one thing, right?

35:33.131 --> 35:35.002
So cool.

35:36.308 --> 35:38.875
You haven't been
in here in a while.

35:38.919 --> 35:40.790
No, I haven't.

35:44.490 --> 35:46.056
What's this one?

35:50.931 --> 35:54.021
Oh, no.

35:54.587 --> 35:56.284
It's, uh, I should
have gotten rid of this.

35:56.893 --> 35:59.461
Who-who is, who is that?

36:00.114 --> 36:01.463
There's no use
dwelling on the past.

36:01.507 --> 36:04.205
You're home now, that's
all that matters, alright?

36:04.249 --> 36:06.947
So I was thinking we could
dust off some canvasses you

36:06.990 --> 36:07.904
know, and see what comes of it.

36:08.731 --> 36:09.906
I'd love to.

36:09.950 --> 36:11.125
Yeah?

36:11.169 --> 36:11.778
Uh, what's your poison?

36:11.821 --> 36:13.083
Oils, watercolors?

36:13.127 --> 36:14.346
I've got it all.

36:14.389 --> 36:16.261
- Charcoal.
- Charcoal.

36:16.304 --> 36:19.133
Okay, pick an object and
we'll sit down

36:19.177 --> 36:21.657
and we'll draw it together.

36:22.180 --> 36:25.095
I want to draw you.

36:25.139 --> 36:26.096
You want to draw me?

36:26.140 --> 36:27.185
Hm-hm.

36:27.228 --> 36:27.837
Allen: Yeah, okay.

36:31.754 --> 36:33.191
Well, this is a first.

36:33.843 --> 36:34.975
How do you want me?

36:35.541 --> 36:37.499
I can, I can do the thinker.

36:38.021 --> 36:39.066
The way you were when
you were looking at that.

36:41.721 --> 36:43.070
That's not a place I
want to live anymore.

36:44.202 --> 36:47.205
There, just like that.

36:54.429 --> 36:55.778
Allen: You learned to paint
while you were over there?

36:55.822 --> 36:58.694
Mm-hm.

37:02.437 --> 37:05.092
Would you just draw, or was
it, was it also..

37:05.135 --> 37:08.269
It wasn't what you think.

37:08.704 --> 37:09.749
Tricia: It's still happening

37:09.792 --> 37:11.794
despite everything
that's going on.

37:11.838 --> 37:12.926
Allen?

37:12.969 --> 37:14.406
No, he won't be there.

37:14.449 --> 37:16.625
You know how he feels
about these things.

37:16.669 --> 37:18.279
So I'll see you at the
gala tomorrow then, okay?

37:18.323 --> 37:19.933
It's for good cause.

37:19.976 --> 37:23.284
Beth, just bring your
checkbook and Jim.

37:23.328 --> 37:25.286
It's for pediatric
cancer, for Christ's sake.

37:25.330 --> 37:28.246
Okay, that's better, thank you.

37:36.776 --> 37:37.951
I'm finished.

37:37.994 --> 37:38.691
Allen; Already?

37:38.734 --> 37:40.432
Hm-hm.

37:45.654 --> 37:46.786
Do you like it?

37:46.829 --> 37:47.874
Allen; I love it.

37:47.917 --> 37:50.006
It's-it's incredible.

37:50.442 --> 37:52.400
Okay, thirty seconds, alright?

37:52.444 --> 37:54.489
And then we're gonna see
what you can do with paint.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.138
Leena: That's private.

38:35.182 --> 38:36.531
Oh, I'm sorry.

38:36.575 --> 38:38.098
I-I saw that you brought it
back with you,

38:38.141 --> 38:39.229
I thought it was special.

38:39.273 --> 38:39.882
You don't knock?

38:41.319 --> 38:44.234
I was looking for my gold watch.

38:44.278 --> 38:47.150
It's OK, I'm sure it
will turn up.

38:47.194 --> 38:48.238
Sorry!

38:54.941 --> 39:00.512
♪

39:15.570 --> 39:17.006
Property of Esther.

39:19.182 --> 39:20.445
Mummy took me to Wicked.

39:20.967 --> 39:22.925
Mummy.

39:22.969 --> 39:24.753
Hello, mummy.

39:25.319 --> 39:26.364
Thank you, mummy.

39:28.888 --> 39:30.411
I know, mummy.

39:31.281 --> 39:32.195
Mummy.

39:34.633 --> 39:36.156
Huh! Mummy.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.165
You're not gonna
believe what Esther can do.

39:45.208 --> 39:48.124
We spent the afternoon
in the studio.

39:48.168 --> 39:50.257
She drew a portrait of me.

39:50.997 --> 39:53.303
She's got more talent than
I had when I was in my 20s.

39:53.347 --> 39:54.566
How's that possible?

39:54.609 --> 39:56.437
Four years ago she was
drawing stick figures.

39:56.481 --> 39:57.395
Easy.

39:57.438 --> 39:58.657
What?

39:58.700 --> 40:00.223
Think about where you
were four years ago.

40:00.267 --> 40:01.573
Now you're a fencing champion.

40:01.616 --> 40:05.054
Yeah, just, it's impressive.

40:05.664 --> 40:07.448
Maybe you can make
a portrait of me.

40:08.101 --> 40:09.363
This is delicious, mummy.

40:10.625 --> 40:13.193
Thank you.

40:14.847 --> 40:15.935
Is something wrong?

40:17.415 --> 40:18.154
No, no.

40:18.198 --> 40:18.981
I'm-I'm just..

40:19.025 --> 40:20.635
[doorbell]

40:20.679 --> 40:23.029
Were you expecting someone?

40:28.948 --> 40:32.299
Male voice: Just thought I'd pop
in to say hi to Esther.

40:32.342 --> 40:33.909
Look who came for a visit.

40:33.953 --> 40:35.389
Oh, I'm sorry to
interrupt dinner.

40:36.521 --> 40:38.305
Allen: This is, uh, the
police officer who helped us

40:38.348 --> 40:39.175
when you went missing.

40:39.219 --> 40:40.612
He's a friend.

40:40.655 --> 40:44.093
Officer: I just came to say
welcome home Esther.

40:44.137 --> 40:45.791
Thank you.

40:48.446 --> 40:50.143
Excuse me for a moment.

40:55.322 --> 40:58.630
Allen: You should know, um, our
child psychologist feels

40:58.673 --> 41:01.589
Esther should tell her story
within the confines of a...

41:01.633 --> 41:02.982
Donnan: And not
with a cop like me.

41:03.025 --> 41:04.984
Don't worry, I get it.

41:05.027 --> 41:07.987
But Esther did vanish from
our little town,

41:08.030 --> 41:10.903
and that remains a concern.

41:10.946 --> 41:12.948
I need to know if
there's still a danger.

41:14.080 --> 41:16.430
I spoke to Dr.
Segar this morning.

41:16.474 --> 41:19.694
Tricia: Is that appropriate?

41:19.738 --> 41:21.740
Donnan; She told me she's
open to a group discussion

41:21.783 --> 41:23.263
tomorrow morning.

41:23.306 --> 41:25.091
Just to see if
everything's alright.

41:25.483 --> 41:29.008
Mummy, your gala is tomorrow.

41:31.576 --> 41:33.142
Donnan: We'll do it the
following day then.

41:33.186 --> 41:34.317
It's important.

41:34.361 --> 41:35.536
I mean, sure.

41:35.580 --> 41:38.191
If it's that important,
we'll be there.

41:39.932 --> 41:42.761
You forgot to
fill your glass.

41:45.285 --> 41:49.202
Well, um, welcome
home, Esther.

41:49.245 --> 41:50.377
You said that already.

41:50.420 --> 41:51.247
Now, Esther.

41:51.291 --> 41:52.988
Oh, it's okay, she's right.

41:53.032 --> 41:54.033
I'll walk you out.

42:00.735 --> 42:03.608
♪ dramatic music

42:26.805 --> 42:28.458
I'm sorry
you live here.

42:28.502 --> 42:30.852
♪

43:24.689 --> 43:27.648
You know.. I think
I'll stay here

43:27.692 --> 43:29.519
for a while.

44:00.376 --> 44:02.074
Tricia: I think something's
going on with Dr. Segar.

44:03.379 --> 44:04.685
She seemed to be implying
in our last meeting

44:04.729 --> 44:06.948
that Esther is lying.

44:08.297 --> 44:10.343
Allen: That's insane.

44:10.386 --> 44:12.040
Maybe she needs to
see a therapist.

44:12.084 --> 44:14.390
I know, right?

44:14.782 --> 44:17.742
What...what is this?

44:17.785 --> 44:18.786
Allen: Your date.

44:18.830 --> 44:19.874
You're coming?

44:19.918 --> 44:20.962
Yeah, of course, I'm coming.

44:21.006 --> 44:22.224
You're my wife.

44:22.268 --> 44:24.270
I can deal with a few
rich pricks for you.

44:24.662 --> 44:25.706
What about Esther?

44:25.750 --> 44:26.576
Well, Gunnar's here.

44:26.620 --> 44:28.404
She'll be fine. Right?

44:28.448 --> 44:29.449
What? Do you want
me to stay home?

44:29.492 --> 44:32.147
No. No.

44:35.107 --> 44:37.413
You know, it seems like
since we got Esther back,

44:37.457 --> 44:40.547
we got us back too.

44:41.766 --> 44:43.855
I couldn't agree more.

44:44.420 --> 44:45.944
Allen: How long do you
need to get dressed?

44:45.987 --> 44:47.162
Tricia: I can be quick.

44:47.206 --> 44:48.381
Yeah?

44:50.426 --> 44:51.514
I can be quick too.

44:57.085 --> 44:59.131
[laughing]

44:59.435 --> 45:00.567
I'm sorry.

45:00.610 --> 45:01.524
No, they're cute.

45:10.664 --> 45:13.711
♪ Tense music

45:30.989 --> 45:31.990
Just close the door.

45:37.691 --> 45:39.040
Just close the door.

45:39.084 --> 45:40.781
What?

45:40.825 --> 45:42.304
No.

45:42.348 --> 45:44.742
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

45:44.785 --> 45:46.047
Oh, my God.

45:46.091 --> 45:48.049
Do you know how much
I spent on this dress.

45:49.181 --> 45:49.877
Let me look.

45:49.921 --> 45:50.965
Oh, man.

45:51.009 --> 45:53.489
I can fix that,
with a safety pin.

45:53.533 --> 45:54.621
Right, or staples.

45:54.664 --> 45:56.318
Staples will work.

46:01.454 --> 46:02.934
Allen: You're responsible for
looking after your sister

46:02.977 --> 46:04.718
while we're gone.

46:04.762 --> 46:06.328
We're trusting you, okay.

46:06.372 --> 46:07.634
Gunnar: Yeah, dad. I got it.

46:09.505 --> 46:10.985
Allen: You look incredible.

46:11.943 --> 46:13.553
We're off.

46:13.596 --> 46:14.728
Tricia: Probably won't be home
till after midnight, okay.

46:14.772 --> 46:17.339
So, don't let her
stay up too late.

46:17.383 --> 46:18.297
You have the keys?

46:18.340 --> 46:20.473
Copy that.

46:27.132 --> 46:28.960
You look nice.

46:29.003 --> 46:30.526
Thanks.

46:31.614 --> 46:33.529
Have a good night, honey.

46:33.878 --> 46:34.443
Ciao.

46:34.487 --> 46:36.271
Night.

46:39.927 --> 46:42.103
So what are we going to do?

46:42.625 --> 46:43.626
We?

46:45.672 --> 46:47.065
Whoo!

46:47.108 --> 46:49.284
[loud partying]

46:56.988 --> 46:58.859
♪ Old singing from
record player ♪

47:09.870 --> 47:11.654
Oh, it's out. Oh, shit,
guys, I'm sorry.

47:11.698 --> 47:13.656
I was holding on
to it for too long.

47:13.700 --> 47:15.571
Okay, is it, Gunnar, is
your sister different

47:15.615 --> 47:17.095
than you remember?

47:17.138 --> 47:18.879
I mean.. What do you think?

47:18.923 --> 47:20.750
She's been at some
eastern European sex gulag.

47:22.404 --> 47:22.927
Mike!

47:22.970 --> 47:24.015
Yeah, no.

47:24.058 --> 47:25.712
She, uh, she's
different, alright.

47:25.755 --> 47:28.323
She's got an accent now.

47:28.367 --> 47:29.890
And she dresses
like Lizzie Borden.

47:29.934 --> 47:32.414
It's so fucking weird.

47:32.458 --> 47:33.807
Who is Lizzie Borden?

47:37.637 --> 47:41.162
Uh, some crazy chick who
killed her parents with an axe.

47:41.206 --> 47:43.904
Uh, hey, Esther.

47:43.948 --> 47:47.821
Why don't you go watch
a movie or something?

47:47.865 --> 47:49.344
No.

47:49.692 --> 47:52.391
Esther, this isn't your scene.

47:52.434 --> 47:54.001
Go watch a movie.

47:54.045 --> 47:55.568
Go fuck yourself.

47:55.611 --> 47:57.265
[jeering laughter]

47:57.309 --> 47:58.136
Hey, Gunnar, you
know what I like.

48:02.357 --> 48:03.968
Go.

48:06.274 --> 48:07.449
Anyway, cheers.

48:07.493 --> 48:08.668
[laughter]

48:08.711 --> 48:09.887
Male: Yeah, I'll fucking
drink to that.

48:14.717 --> 48:15.501
What were we talking about?

48:15.544 --> 48:17.938
[doorbell and knocking]

48:20.854 --> 48:22.464
Evening.

48:23.596 --> 48:25.815
Hey, my parents aren't here.

48:25.859 --> 48:27.469
They're at mom's gala.

48:27.513 --> 48:28.993
Just my luck.

48:29.036 --> 48:31.125
Having a party?

48:31.169 --> 48:33.345
No, it's just a few friends.

48:33.823 --> 48:35.477
You can smell the
weed from the street.

48:35.521 --> 48:37.044
What?

48:37.088 --> 48:39.220
Uh, I don't know, I don't know
what you're talking about.

48:41.744 --> 48:43.877
Look, nothing's
going on here, okay?

48:43.921 --> 48:46.706
So, um, why don't I just tell
my parents that you stopped by

48:46.749 --> 48:48.926
and we can just
forget all about this?

48:49.796 --> 48:51.798
Cool?

48:51.841 --> 48:52.886
Cool.

48:53.452 --> 48:55.323
Good.

48:55.889 --> 48:57.717
Mind if I hit the
restroom before I go?

48:59.545 --> 49:01.373
Yeah. Um, whatever, yeah, sure.

49:02.722 --> 49:06.204
[party music plays]

49:08.902 --> 49:12.732
[scratching from record player]

49:15.691 --> 49:21.001
♪ expectant music

49:35.407 --> 49:38.976
♪ dramatic music

50:21.322 --> 50:22.802
Allen: That was a blast.

50:22.845 --> 50:24.586
No wonder those uptight
millionaires line up to give

50:24.630 --> 50:26.501
the foundation money.

50:27.111 --> 50:29.417
Oh, no. It's the booze.

50:29.461 --> 50:30.853
It's not the booze, hon.

50:30.897 --> 50:32.420
It's the host.

50:32.464 --> 50:33.639
You bring the best
out of people.

50:33.682 --> 50:35.075
Aww!

50:35.119 --> 50:37.904
♪ dramatic music

50:53.180 --> 50:55.226
I just hope the house
is still standing.

50:55.269 --> 50:59.317
I mean when I was
16, I-I nearly,

50:59.360 --> 51:01.536
I nearly burned the house down.

51:01.971 --> 51:03.495
No, Gunnar would never do that.

51:03.538 --> 51:05.453
Who says I'm talking
about Gunnar?

51:05.497 --> 51:07.586
[laughter]

51:10.154 --> 51:11.807
Esther? We're home.

51:14.506 --> 51:15.289
Esther?

51:15.333 --> 51:19.250
[shower running]

51:51.282 --> 51:55.634
♪ tense music

52:11.563 --> 52:13.347
The Saarne Institute?

52:25.011 --> 52:27.492
Esther?

52:27.535 --> 52:30.495
♪ dramatic music

53:25.027 --> 53:27.465
[creaking door closes]

53:43.132 --> 53:45.700
[dog barks]

54:15.730 --> 54:17.645
If you're not Esther,
who the hell are you?

54:19.256 --> 54:23.260
[dramatic music sting and
stabbing sounds]

54:34.706 --> 54:36.621
How did you know
that I'm not Esther?

54:42.366 --> 54:44.281
Her own mother
doesn't even know.

54:45.282 --> 54:46.848
[choking]

54:46.892 --> 54:48.285
Yeah, kid, she does.

54:49.068 --> 54:52.811
[gunshots]

54:58.469 --> 54:59.774
Damn it.

55:00.166 --> 55:01.689
Mummy?

55:02.560 --> 55:03.909
What the fuck are
you looking at?

55:07.782 --> 55:10.263
Tricia: So, let me
get this straight.

55:10.872 --> 55:12.831
You're a grown-ass woman
and a wanted criminal?

55:14.398 --> 55:17.401
That is...beyond fucked up.

55:21.361 --> 55:24.016
This is all I ever do
anymore by the way.

55:24.059 --> 55:25.757
Clean up after my kids.

55:26.148 --> 55:26.975
Don't worry about it.

55:27.019 --> 55:28.455
Mommy will take care of it.

55:28.499 --> 55:30.327
Mommy takes care of everything.

55:31.502 --> 55:33.373
When Gunnar told me
Donnan came to the house,

55:33.417 --> 55:35.070
I knew I'd find you here.

55:36.463 --> 55:39.248
You could've robbed us blind
and disappeared the second you

55:39.292 --> 55:41.990
had a chance, but you didn't.

55:44.036 --> 55:45.385
Why is that?

55:46.473 --> 55:48.170
You're thinking bigger.

55:48.214 --> 55:49.911
Right?

55:49.955 --> 55:53.393
Play the part, manipulate us..
And a year from now we meet

55:53.437 --> 55:55.569
with some tragic accident.

55:55.613 --> 55:57.092
Am I getting warm?

55:57.571 --> 55:59.225
Let me go.

55:59.268 --> 56:01.096
You'll never see me again.

56:01.140 --> 56:03.055
Tricia: That's exactly
what I'm afraid of.

56:03.098 --> 56:05.623
We can't have Esther
disappear twice now, can we?

56:06.928 --> 56:09.148
She didn't disappear.

56:09.191 --> 56:11.759
There was nothing that
I could do for her.

56:11.803 --> 56:13.282
It was too late.

56:14.893 --> 56:19.114
Gunnar.. He was always
way too rough with her.

56:19.158 --> 56:20.899
That night it
just went too far.

56:21.508 --> 56:23.945
What was I supposed to do?

56:23.989 --> 56:27.949
Hand over the only child I had
left over some sibling bullshit

56:27.993 --> 56:29.560
that went too far?

56:30.387 --> 56:33.259
I loved my daughter,
with all my heart.

56:33.302 --> 56:36.436
But a mother protects her
family, no matter what.

56:36.480 --> 56:41.223
