your teeth for days.

1:01:54.101 --> 1:01:56.756
In summary Esther exhibits
a healthy outlook on life.

1:01:56.800 --> 1:02:00.325
Especially re-entering
into this family unit.

1:02:00.368 --> 1:02:02.153
She's highly functioning.

1:02:02.196 --> 1:02:04.764
Emotionally well.

1:02:04.808 --> 1:02:06.723
That is all.

1:02:09.203 --> 1:02:10.944
There are people
coming over today.

1:02:10.988 --> 1:02:13.599
Just to see you.

1:02:15.122 --> 1:02:18.778
They're friends of ours, who
knew Esther, so, enough with

1:02:18.822 --> 1:02:21.520
the glowering, okay?

1:02:21.563 --> 1:02:24.392
Esther is a lady.

1:02:25.480 --> 1:02:29.615
Hmm.

1:02:29.658 --> 1:02:31.095
I think I'm gonna
have to do some damage.

1:02:35.012 --> 1:02:37.536
Okay.

1:02:38.667 --> 1:02:40.234
I think we did good.

1:02:40.278 --> 1:02:42.802
Everyone expects
Esther to be broken.

1:02:42.846 --> 1:02:45.936
What they really want
is a happy ending.

1:02:45.979 --> 1:02:49.461
We are gonna pretend that
pink is your favorite color.

1:02:50.462 --> 1:02:52.246
Ooh, velvet.

1:02:52.290 --> 1:02:53.813
The secret.

1:02:53.857 --> 1:02:56.598
Let's give them a story
they want to believe.

1:02:57.338 --> 1:02:59.906
This one is my favorite.

1:02:59.950 --> 1:03:00.777
What's your favorite color?

1:03:00.820 --> 1:03:02.343
Pink.

1:03:02.387 --> 1:03:04.041
Very, very good.

1:03:05.782 --> 1:03:09.524
Now, you say you can paint.

1:03:09.568 --> 1:03:10.787
What else can you do?

1:03:12.049 --> 1:03:14.312
[Piano plays classical music.]

1:03:27.064 --> 1:03:28.848
I missed my
family very much.

1:03:28.892 --> 1:03:31.590
It's lovely to be back.

1:03:31.633 --> 1:03:34.593
And what are your
plans now, young lady?

1:03:35.637 --> 1:03:38.162
What are my plans, mummy?

1:03:38.205 --> 1:03:40.077
Absolutely nothing.

1:03:40.120 --> 1:03:42.993
I'm not letting you
out of my sight.

1:04:07.104 --> 1:04:09.846
So let me
get this straight.

1:04:09.889 --> 1:04:11.369
You're 30?

1:04:11.412 --> 1:04:13.197
Get out of my room,
now, please.

1:04:13.240 --> 1:04:14.459
It's not your room.

1:04:14.502 --> 1:04:16.026
It's my dead sister's room.

1:04:16.069 --> 1:04:17.897
You're not her and
you never will be.

1:04:17.941 --> 1:04:19.377
Is that perfectly clear?

1:04:19.420 --> 1:04:20.595
Fuck off.

1:04:20.639 --> 1:04:22.684
Watch your mouth, freak.

1:04:22.728 --> 1:04:25.513
You know, I'm glad everything's
out in the open now.

1:04:25.557 --> 1:04:26.993
'Cause I'm done pretending
like you belong here.

1:04:27.037 --> 1:04:28.865
You don't.

1:04:29.953 --> 1:04:32.912
This is my house, my family.

1:04:32.956 --> 1:04:35.001
And it will never be yours.

1:04:35.045 --> 1:04:36.133
As long as you're
under this roof,

1:04:36.176 --> 1:04:38.178
you and I will have an
understanding.

1:04:38.222 --> 1:04:39.353
Here's what it is.

1:04:42.313 --> 1:04:44.793
I fucking own you.

1:04:44.837 --> 1:04:47.361
[slap]

1:04:47.405 --> 1:04:49.015
Do that again and I'll kill
you like I killed Esther.

1:04:49.059 --> 1:04:50.669
[slap]

1:04:50.712 --> 1:04:53.237
[laughs]

1:04:53.280 --> 1:04:56.718
One call from me, and you're
right back in that gulag.

1:04:56.762 --> 1:04:58.633
You'd go down too.

1:04:58.677 --> 1:05:01.245
Why, because of what the
illegal immigrant fugitive

1:05:01.288 --> 1:05:02.724
mental patient said?

1:05:04.465 --> 1:05:08.643
Good luck with that.

1:05:08.687 --> 1:05:10.167
This is America.

1:05:10.210 --> 1:05:12.604
People like me matter.

1:05:12.647 --> 1:05:14.693
And if you're not Esther,
ah, it just means

1:05:14.736 --> 1:05:16.347
Esther's missing again.

1:05:16.390 --> 1:05:18.175
Mom has a problem with that.

1:05:18.218 --> 1:05:20.960
I don't.

1:05:21.004 --> 1:05:22.701
See you later, freak.

1:05:29.664 --> 1:05:33.538
You are gonna sleep
like a fucking baby tonight.

1:05:35.627 --> 1:05:39.457
I made roast lamb
with rosemary and tapenade.

1:05:39.500 --> 1:05:41.024
And I know, Esther
doesn't like it.

1:05:41.067 --> 1:05:42.460
So I made your favorite.

1:05:42.503 --> 1:05:44.984
Oh, just like the old days.

1:05:45.028 --> 1:05:48.118
I'm really excited about
going into the city tomorrow.

1:05:48.161 --> 1:05:50.859
I'm gonna show the gallery
what I've been working on.

1:05:51.904 --> 1:05:53.993
That sounds wonderful.

1:05:54.037 --> 1:05:55.125
Well, it's all thanks to you.

1:05:55.168 --> 1:05:56.691
Oh.

1:05:56.735 --> 1:05:58.345
I rediscovered the joy I once
felt doing what I loved.

1:05:58.389 --> 1:05:59.868
I feel like a kid again.

1:05:59.912 --> 1:06:00.695
Do you wanna come?

1:06:00.739 --> 1:06:01.783
I would love to!

1:06:01.827 --> 1:06:04.003
Oh, Esther and I
already have plans.

1:06:04.047 --> 1:06:06.179
Oh.

1:06:06.223 --> 1:06:08.529
What plans?

1:06:08.573 --> 1:06:10.227
It's a surprise.

1:06:10.270 --> 1:06:11.184
Okay.

1:06:11.228 --> 1:06:13.970
